{"parentUuid":"c5c0aa7a-9e5b-4f44-976a-34fcafb2f9f1","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a89b1e9e76596c6d2","type":"progress","data":{"type":"hook_progress","hookEvent":"PostToolUse","hookName":"PostToolUse:Read","command":"callback"},"parentToolUseID":"call_lNXg0q4UFdKVGdGMi11SRHoH","toolUseID":"call_lNXg0q4UFdKVGdGMi11SRHoH","timestamp":"2026-03-17T18:48:16.293Z","uuid":"5a1da258-db1f-427f-8285-d215048bde07","userType":"external","cwd":"/config/workspace/IronClaude","sessionId":"caf57f20-b6f0-47d7-a404-b3840c9c44e5","version":"2.1.77","gitBranch":"v3.0-AuditGates","slug":"bright-juggling-reef"}
{"parentUuid":"cbb9911d-2549-4e36-a1c2-20f82dd83c81","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a89b1e9e76596c6d2","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_lNXg0q4UFdKVGdGMi11SRHoH","type":"tool_result","content":"   946→```\n   947→\n   948→### Enforcement Strategy\n   949→\n   950→<!-- Source: V1-C (spec structural audit), adapted per refactor-plan -->\n   951→\n   952→Phase 1 (immediate): Warning-only. The executor logs a warning if the ratio falls below 0.5 but does not block the pipeline. This allows shadow-mode validation on real specs before enforcement.\n   953→\n   954→Phase 2 (after validation): STRICT enforcement. If the structural count suggests the extraction is missing significant content, the executor re-triggers extraction or halts with an actionable error.\n   955→\n   956→---\n   957→\n   958→## 8. Gate Definition\n   959→\n   960→<!-- Source: Merge (new content bridging V2+V5) -->\n   961→\n   962→### New Gate: `ANTI_INSTINCT_GATE`\n   963→\n   964→**File**: `src/superclaude/cli/roadmap/gates.py` (modify existing)\n   965→\n   966→```python\n   967→# --- Anti-Instinct Gate check functions ---\n   968→\n   969→def _no_undischarged_obligations(content: str) -> bool:\n   970→    \"\"\"Verify all scaffolding obligations in early phases are discharged by later phases.\n   971→\n   972→    Runs V2-A obligation scanner on the anti-instinct audit report content.\n   973→    The actual scan has already been performed by the executor; this check\n   974→    validates the frontmatter result.\n   975→    \"\"\"\n   976→    fm = _parse_frontmatter(content)\n   977→    if fm is None:\n   978→        return False\n   979→    try:\n   980→        return int(fm.get(\"undischarged_obligations\", -1)) == 0\n   981→    except (ValueError, TypeError):\n   982→        return False\n   983→\n   984→\n   985→def _integration_contracts_covered(content: str) -> bool:\n   986→    \"\"\"Verify all integration contracts from spec are covered in roadmap.\n   987→\n   988→    This check requires both spec and roadmap content. Since semantic\n   989→    checks receive only a single content string, the real enforcement\n   990→    happens in the executor. This validates the executor's written result.\n   991→    \"\"\"\n   992→    fm = _parse_frontmatter(content)\n   993→    if fm is None:\n   994→        return False\n   995→    try:\n   996→        return int(fm.get(\"uncovered_contracts\", -1)) == 0\n   997→    except (ValueError, TypeError):\n   998→        return False\n   999→\n  1000→\n  1001→def _fingerprint_coverage_check(content: str) -> bool:\n  1002→    \"\"\"Verify spec code-level identifiers have sufficient roadmap coverage.\n  1003→\n  1004→    This check requires both spec and roadmap content. Since semantic\n  1005→    checks receive only a single content string, the real enforcement\n  1006→    happens in the executor. This validates the executor's written result.\n  1007→    \"\"\"\n  1008→    fm = _parse_frontmatter(content)\n  1009→    if fm is None:\n  1010→        return False\n  1011→    try:\n  1012→        return float(fm.get(\"fingerprint_coverage\", 0.0)) >= 0.7\n  1013→    except (ValueError, TypeError):\n  1014→        return False\n  1015→\n  1016→\n  1017→# --- Gate definition ---\n  1018→\n  1019→ANTI_INSTINCT_GATE = GateCriteria(\n  1020→    required_frontmatter_fields=[\n  1021→        \"undischarged_obligations\",    # V2-A: integer count\n  1022→        \"uncovered_contracts\",         # V5-1: integer count\n  1023→        \"fingerprint_coverage\",        # V4-2: float 0.0-1.0\n  1024→    ],\n  1025→    min_lines=10,\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"uuid":"18b79e7f-2ac7-4f9d-ae57-c955ca69f3d3","timestamp":"2026-03-17T18:48:16.293Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"cbb9911d-2549-4e36-a1c2-20f82dd83c81","userType":"external","cwd":"/config/workspace/IronClaude","sessionId":"caf57f20-b6f0-47d7-a404-b3840c9c44e5","version":"2.1.77","gitBranch":"v3.0-AuditGates","slug":"bright-juggling-reef"}
{"parentUuid":"18b79e7f-2ac7-4f9d-ae57-c955ca69f3d3","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a89b1e9e76596c6d2","type":"progress","data":{"type":"hook_progress","hookEvent":"PostToolUse","hookName":"PostToolUse:Read","command":"callback"},"parentToolUseID":"call_ZpKxJ4iRB0PosxY0gCtaF26E","toolUseID":"call_ZpKxJ4iRB0PosxY0gCtaF26E","timestamp":"2026-03-17T18:48:16.292Z","uuid":"bf6cbf2e-bc17-4240-bbca-f1fe972d92f1","userType":"external","cwd":"/config/workspace/IronClaude","sessionId":"caf57f20-b6f0-47d7-a404-b3840c9c44e5","version":"2.1.77","gitBranch":"v3.0-AuditGates","slug":"bright-juggling-reef"}
{"parentUuid":"178e33f1-5e0b-44f6-83e7-d9e0b4c42480","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a89b1e9e76596c6d2","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_ZpKxJ4iRB0PosxY0gCtaF26E","type":"tool_result","content":"  1074→\n  1075→The `MERGE_GATE` validates the merge step's output quality (heading hierarchy, cross-refs, duplicates). The anti-instinct checks validate cross-artifact semantic fidelity -- a different concern. Keeping them separate follows the existing pattern where each gate corresponds to one validation concern. The `MERGE_GATE` runs on the merged roadmap; the `ANTI_INSTINCT_GATE` runs on the anti-instinct audit report produced by the executor.\n  1076→\n  1077→### Anti-Instinct Audit Report Format\n  1078→\n  1079→The executor produces `output_dir / \"anti-instinct-audit.md\"` with frontmatter:\n  1080→\n  1081→```yaml\n  1082→---\n  1083→undischarged_obligations: 0\n  1084→uncovered_contracts: 0\n  1085→fingerprint_coverage: 0.85\n  1086→total_obligations: 3\n  1087→discharged_obligations: 3\n  1088→total_contracts: 2\n  1089→covered_contracts: 2\n  1090→total_fingerprints: 15\n  1091→matched_fingerprints: 13\n  1092→structural_audit_passed: true\n  1093→---\n  1094→```\n  1095→\n  1096→This file is the gate artifact. The `ANTI_INSTINCT_GATE` validates its frontmatter fields. The executor writes it after running all three deterministic checks.\n  1097→\n  1098→---\n  1099→\n  1100→## 9. Executor Integration\n  1101→\n  1102→<!-- Source: Merge (new content bridging V2+V5) -->\n  1103→\n  1104→### File: `src/superclaude/cli/roadmap/executor.py` (modify existing)\n  1105→\n  1106→#### Change 1: Structural Audit After Extract\n  1107→\n  1108→**Location**: After `EXTRACT_GATE` passes, before `generate-*` steps.\n  1109→\n  1110→This is NOT a new pipeline Step. It is executor-level logic that runs between steps, following the existing pattern of `_inject_pipeline_diagnostics` after extract.\n  1111→\n  1112→```python\n  1113→# In executor.py, after extract gate passes:\n  1114→from .spec_structural_audit import check_extraction_adequacy\n  1115→\n  1116→def _run_structural_audit(config, output_dir):\n  1117→    \"\"\"Post-extract structural audit (V1-C upstream guard).\n  1118→\n  1119→    Compares spec structural indicators against extraction requirement\n  1120→    count. Phase 1: warning-only.\n  1121→    \"\"\"\n  1122→    import yaml\n  1123→\n  1124→    spec_text = config.spec_file.read_text(encoding=\"utf-8\")\n  1125→    extraction_path = output_dir / \"extraction.md\"\n  1126→    extraction_text = extraction_path.read_text(encoding=\"utf-8\")\n  1127→\n  1128→    # Parse extraction frontmatter for total_requirements\n  1129→    fm_match = re.match(r\"^---\\n(.*?)\\n---\", extraction_text, re.DOTALL)\n  1130→    total_requirements = 0\n  1131→    if fm_match:\n  1132→        try:\n  1133→            fm = yaml.safe_load(fm_match.group(1))\n  1134→            total_requirements = int(fm.get(\"total_requirements\", 0))\n  1135→        except (yaml.YAMLError, ValueError, TypeError):\n  1136→            pass\n  1137→\n  1138→    passed, audit = check_extraction_adequacy(spec_text, total_requirements)\n  1139→    if not passed:\n  1140→        logger.warning(\n  1141→            \"Spec structural audit: extraction may be incomplete. \"\n  1142→            f\"Spec has {audit.total_structural_indicators} structural indicators \"\n  1143→            f\"but extraction reports only {total_requirements} requirements \"\n  1144→            f\"(ratio: {total_requirements / max(audit.total_structural_indicators, 1):.2f}, \"\n  1145→            f\"threshold: 0.5). Consider re-running extraction.\"\n  1146→        )\n  1147→    return passed, audit\n  1148→```\n  1149→\n  1150→#### Change 2: Anti-Instinct Audit Step After Merge\n  1151→\n  1152→**Location**: Between `merge` Step and `test-strategy` Step in `_build_steps()`.\n  1153→\n  1154→This is a non-LLM step. The executor handles it specially (runs Python logic instead of a subprocess) when `step.id == \"anti-instinct\"`. The step appears in the pipeline step list for progress reporting and halt diagnostics.\n  1155→\n  1156→```python\n  1157→# Add to _build_steps() between merge and test-strategy:\n  1158→Step(\n  1159→    id=\"anti-instinct\",\n  1160→    prompt=\"\",  # Non-LLM step; executor handles directly\n  1161→    output_file=out / \"anti-instinct-audit.md\",\n  1162→    gate=ANTI_INSTINCT_GATE,\n  1163→    timeout_seconds=30,  # Pure Python, <1s expected\n  1164→    inputs=[config.spec_file, extraction, merge_file],\n  1165→    retry_limit=0,  # Deterministic; retry would produce same result\n  1166→),\n  1167→```\n  1168→\n  1169→#### Change 3: Anti-Instinct Audit Runner\n  1170→\n  1171→```python\n  1172→from .obligation_scanner import scan_obligations\n  1173→from .integration_contracts import extract_integration_contracts, check_roadmap_coverage\n  1174→from .fingerprint import check_fingerprint_coverage\n  1175→\n  1176→def _run_anti_instinct_audit(config, output_dir):\n  1177→    \"\"\"Run all three deterministic anti-instinct checks.\n  1178→\n  1179→    Reads spec, extraction, and merged roadmap. Runs:\n  1180→    1. V2-A obligation scanner on roadmap content\n  1181→    2. V5-1 integration contract extractor on spec + roadmap\n  1182→    3. V4-2 fingerprint coverage on spec + roadmap\n  1183→\n  1184→    Writes anti-instinct-audit.md with frontmatter for gate validation.\n  1185→    \"\"\"\n  1186→    spec_text = config.spec_file.read_text(encoding=\"utf-8\")\n  1187→    roadmap_path = output_dir / \"roadmap.md\"\n  1188→    roadmap_text = roadmap_path.read_text(encoding=\"utf-8\")\n  1189→\n  1190→    # 1. Obligation scanner (V2-A) -- single-file, roadmap only\n  1191→    obligation_report = scan_obligations(roadmap_text)\n  1192→\n  1193→    # 2. Integration contracts (V5-1) -- spec + roadmap\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"uuid":"6170334c-60a0-4474-9ea7-02910dba5fe4","timestamp":"2026-03-17T18:48:16.292Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"178e33f1-5e0b-44f6-83e7-d9e0b4c42480","userType":"external","cwd":"/config/workspace/IronClaude","sessionId":"caf57f20-b6f0-47d7-a404-b3840c9c44e5","version":"2.1.77","gitBranch":"v3.0-AuditGates","slug":"bright-juggling-reef"}
