{"parentUuid":"07d8e4c9-ac63-45c6-b452-1f90d40d6623","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a89b1e9e76596c6d2","type":"progress","data":{"type":"hook_progress","hookEvent":"PostToolUse","hookName":"PostToolUse:Grep","command":"callback"},"parentToolUseID":"call_ySVPQ5dWXZbEYbc3PJuLAcDY","toolUseID":"call_ySVPQ5dWXZbEYbc3PJuLAcDY","timestamp":"2026-03-17T18:48:32.501Z","uuid":"1773c817-bd9a-44bb-9541-6ffe557cabe5","userType":"external","cwd":"/config/workspace/IronClaude","sessionId":"caf57f20-b6f0-47d7-a404-b3840c9c44e5","version":"2.1.77","gitBranch":"v3.0-AuditGates","slug":"bright-juggling-reef"}
{"parentUuid":"07d8e4c9-ac63-45c6-b452-1f90d40d6623","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a89b1e9e76596c6d2","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_ySVPQ5dWXZbEYbc3PJuLAcDY","type":"tool_result","content":"22:The Anti-Instincts Gate is a unified deterministic defense layer that addresses four failure modes simultaneously:\n61:The `SPEC_FIDELITY_GATE` enforces `high_severity_count == 0` deterministically, but the LLM generating the severity counts shared the same blindspot as the generator. The deterministic enforcement was sound; the LLM input to that gate was wrong.\n101:**Key design property**: All four detection modules are pure Python with zero LLM calls. This is deliberate -- LLM-on-LLM review shares the same blindspots that caused the original bug. The deterministic floor cannot be bypassed by completion bias.\n111:A deterministic, regex-based post-generation pass that scans the merged roadmap for scaffolding terms and verifies each has a corresponding discharge task in a later phase. Catches the failure mode where early phases use \"mocked\", \"stub\", \"skeleton\", \"placeholder\" language that creates implicit obligations that later phases never fulfill.\n367:A deterministic pre-validation step that extracts \"integration contracts\" from the spec and verifies each has a corresponding explicit task in the roadmap. An integration contract is any place where a data structure maps identifiers to callables, a constructor accepts injectable dependencies, an explicit wiring step is described, or a lookup/dispatch mechanism is defined.\n828:A deterministic upstream guard between the spec input and the extraction output. It catches the case where the extraction LLM itself drops requirements before they ever reach the roadmap. Neither the obligation scanner, contract extractor, nor fingerprint check can detect this -- all downstream checks are vacuous if extraction drops a requirement.\n1096:This file is the gate artifact. The `ANTI_INSTINCT_GATE` validates its frontmatter fields. The executor writes it after running all three deterministic checks.\n1163:    timeout_seconds=30,  # Pure Python, <1s expected\n1165:    retry_limit=0,  # Deterministic; retry would produce same result\n1177:    \"\"\"Run all three deterministic anti-instinct checks.\n1372:| X-007 | V3 vs V4 on enforcement tier | Deterministic checks (V2-A, V5-1, V4-2) get STRICT enforcement (zero false-positive risk on true positives). Heuristic checks (future V3-1) get TRAILING initially. |\n1408:- **Pipeline latency added**: <1s (combined deterministic execution)\n1446:| Negative-space prompting (with V1-E structured output schema) | V4-3 + V1-E | After Phase 1 deterministic checks validated in shadow mode (3+ pipeline runs with zero false positives) |\n1466:| A-010 | LLM tendencies are correlated | Joint miss-rate optimistic | All Phase 1 checks are deterministic (not LLM), so correlation between LLM tendencies is irrelevant |\n1495:| Negative-space prompting | V4-3 | Adds LLM call cost; deferred until deterministic checks validated |\n\n[Showing results with pagination = limit: 120, offset: 0]"}]},"uuid":"029091cf-56ce-4e87-8205-0efeebd21163","timestamp":"2026-03-17T18:48:32.501Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"07d8e4c9-ac63-45c6-b452-1f90d40d6623","userType":"external","cwd":"/config/workspace/IronClaude","sessionId":"caf57f20-b6f0-47d7-a404-b3840c9c44e5","version":"2.1.77","gitBranch":"v3.0-AuditGates","slug":"bright-juggling-reef"}
